I'm sorry about what happened.

253
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:49,567
I wasn't able to control myself.

254
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:54,267
Well, a little self-control
might have worked,

255
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:57,167
but it wasn't your fault.

256
00:17:58,133 --> 00:18:00,700
It was Bok who came here
and caused trouble.

257
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:03,933
As for you,
you did everything you could.

258
00:18:03,933 --> 00:18:06,167
You made this event possible.

259
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:08,967
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

260
00:18:08,967 --> 00:18:10,133
Even so.

261
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:13,967
This is what I've been
telling you, Martin.

262
00:18:14,867 --> 00:18:15,967
Told me what?

263
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:20,900
That my life is a mess.

264
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,067
You shouldn't be
dragged into it.

265
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,167
We shouldn't be dragged
into it,

266
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:28,167
but we should always
help each other.

267
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:30,967
Thank you.

268
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:34,567
Wait.

269
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:36,900
Where's Kiko?

270
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:39,200
I haven't seen him
since earlier.

271
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,967
Maybe he's at the venue.
Why don't you call him?

272
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:47,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:53,167
[LINE RINGING]

274
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:55,333
- He's not picking up.
- He's not?

275
00:18:55,367 --> 00:19:01,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

276
00:19:07,767 --> 00:19:08,667
Thank you.

277
00:19:09,467 --> 00:19:11,267
- Are you a local?
- Yes, sir.

278
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,167
Really?

279
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,533
- You grew up here?
- Yes, sir.

280
00:19:14,667 --> 00:19:15,600
Do you know this person?

281
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,567
Um, no, sir.

282
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:20,867
- Are you sure?
- Yes, sir.

283
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,833
Okay. Thank you.

284
00:19:22,967 --> 00:19:24,100
Enjoy, sir.

285
00:19:25,967 --> 00:19:28,733
[UPBEAT MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

286
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:33,367
Bro! Have fun, okay?

287
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:36,067
If you need anything,
I'm right here.

288
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:38,200
- Just one call away.
- Sure, bro.

289
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:39,833
This is so far, fun, Edward.

290
00:19:39,967 --> 00:19:41,700
I got you, I got you.

291
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:45,067
It's gonna start in a minute.

292
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:48,800
- Hi!
- Hi!

293
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:51,300
Edward, can we take a selfie?

294
00:19:52,333 --> 00:19:53,833
[LUNA] Yeah, that's good.

295
00:19:53,967 --> 00:19:56,533
Also, can you fix the barricade
at the north entrance?

296
00:19:56,667 --> 00:19:58,400
It's broken down.
We can't let that stay that way.

297
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:00,333
- Copy, ma'am.
- How about the wristbands?

298
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:02,100
We've fixed that issue, ma'am.

299
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:04,833
Yeah, make sure
everyone gets one.

300
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,233
Are you alright, Ma'am Luna?

301
00:20:09,267 --> 00:20:11,733
Yeah. There's just so much
going on right now.

302
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:14,833
I had to deal with something
back at the hotel earlier.

303
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:16,500
Ma'am, why don't you
get some rest?

304
00:20:16,933 --> 00:20:18,367
Not right now.

305
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,900
Go on now. And keep me updated.

306
00:20:20,033 --> 00:20:21,167
Yes, ma'am.

307
00:20:24,267 --> 00:20:26,300
She probably just went
to a supplier.

308
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:28,433
Who?

309
00:20:28,567 --> 00:20:29,367
Jade.

310
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,900
You're looking for her, right?

311
00:20:31,033 --> 00:20:32,200
She's on her way.

312
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:34,400
Yeah, I'm looking for her.

313
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:36,700
Where is she?

314
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:43,767
[PANTING]

315
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:49,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

316
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:10,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

317
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:20,400
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

318
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:27,867
[COUGHS]

319
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:40,300
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:50,333
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [JADE PANTING]

321
00:21:53,367 --> 00:21:55,967
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

322
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:06,600
<i> Someone took Jade.</i>

323
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,633
<i>No matter what happens,
Mom should be safe at home.</i>

324
00:22:08,633 --> 00:22:09,733
<i> No, Jade!</i>

325
00:22:09,733 --> 00:22:11,733
<i>- What about my brother?
- We won't abandon Kiko.</i>

326
00:22:11,733 --> 00:22:12,667
<i> He's also our brother, okay?</i>

327
00:22:12,667 --> 00:22:14,467
<i>Make sure everything
runs smoothly.</i>

328
00:22:14,467 --> 00:22:15,600
<i> That monster!</i>

329
00:22:15,633 --> 00:22:17,733
<i>It's possible he's obsessed
with Mrs. Almazan,</i>

330
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,433
<i>and he was mad
at your fathers.</i>

331
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:20,500
<i> Where's Trixie?</i>

332
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:24,133
<i> I saw her leave
with Miss Cheska and Sari.</i>

333
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:25,500
<i>- Hey!
- Aah!</i>

334
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:27,800
<i>I can't lose another member
of my family again.</i>

335
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:28,900
<i>- Mom! Mom!
- Mom!</i>

336
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:30,567
<i>We're also checking
this area.</i>

337
00:22:30,567 --> 00:22:32,767
<i>We might find something that
could help us find them.</i>

338
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:34,833
<i>We'll go to whichever
island it is.</i>

339
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:36,567
<i> I'll confront Roi myself.</i>

340
00:22:36,567 --> 00:22:38,033
<i> Police!</i>

341
00:22:38,033 --> 00:22:39,033
[TIRES SCREECHING]

342
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,067
<i> I love your mother.</i>

343
00:22:43,067 --> 00:22:47,033
<i>I'm willing to die
and kill for her.</i>

